					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Stop doing bad publicity for the SNES sound, which is able of more than this, I'm pretty sure, even when it comes to do techno. Most early SNES games use the hardware pretty badly, because good samples at high sampling rate takes a lot of space, and most games have only one set of samples they write once in memory and never touches again, greatly limiting the number of available samples (and quality too) as opposed to games that change samples for each song as they need them.
<br />
<br />You could rather listen the soundtrack in Chrono Trigger, and then you'll see that it puts the Megadrive to shame.</div>

